A '''wayside pulpit''' is a roadside sign fronting [[church]]es and other [[Religion|religious]] worship centers, whose message is changed regularly, often weekly, and is typically welcoming or scriptural, [[philosophy|philosophical]], spiritual, or otherwise uplifting quotations.

Among denominations, [[Unitarian Universalist]]s are the ones who most commonly use the term for their message marquees.   The [[Unitarian Universalist Association]] has provided 
congregations and communities spiritual refreshment in the form 
of the ''Wayside Community Pulpit'' for four decades.

